title: Missing teenager Celeste Smith found safe and well
text:
Celeste Smith has now been found safe and well. Credit: Devon and Cornwall Police A teenager who was missing from Saltash has now been found safe and well and has been reunited with her family.
19-year-old Celeste Smith went missing last Tuesday evening after finding out she was pregnant.
Police have now released an update saying she has been found and the officers involved in efforts to locate her would like to thank the public for their help and support.
DevonCornwall Police @DC_Police Follow Police confirm that Celeste Smith has been found safe and well this afternoon reunited with family. Thank you to all for help & support.
17:56 - 6 Feb 2017 Retweet Reply Favourite Celeste's cousin Katy has also thanked those who searched for her including her friends.
She left this message on Facebook.
Celeste's cousin Katy left this message on Facebook Credit: Katy Smith Facebook Celeste's friends had been helping in the search for her which had begun to centre on Plymouth where they were handing out flyers and raising awareness of her disappearance.
